name: Fox News
summary: Several recent news articles have focused on the 2020 presidential election and related issues. Fox News reports that Trump has filed a $10 billion defamation lawsuit against CBS News, alleging that they deceptively edited an interview with Kamala Harris for "60 Minutes." Polls conducted by Fox News indicate that Trump is narrowly ahead of Harris in North Carolina, while Harris has erased Trump's lead on the economy in Michigan. The race remains neck-and-neck in Pennsylvania. Additionally, the White House has been accused of altering a transcript of a Biden speech despite concerns from stenographers. Other articles highlight that Harris has not held a formal press conference since becoming the Democratic nominee, and that Trump wore a garbage worker vest at a rally in a critical swing state. There are also reports of an investigation into a Pennsylvania probe involving a company linked to fraudulent voter applications in Arizona. Lastly, a judge in Pennsylvania has allowed Elon Musk's PAC to continue its $1 million a day giveaway.

Health experts have expressed concern about the potential impact of Kennedy's influence on public health policy, citing his anti-vaccine stance and support for unproven claims about fluoride's harmful effects. The stock's decline has also caused Trump's net worth to slump by $1.9 billion. As Kamala Harris gains in election polls, the DJT rally has faltered, contributing to the stock's losses. name: Jonathan Mingo
summary: The Dallas Cowboys have acquired wide receiver Jonathan Mingo from the Carolina Panthers in exchange for a 2025 fourth-round pick. The trade has been met with mixed reactions, with some analysts praising the Cowboys for adding a talented receiver while others question the value they gave up for him. Mingo, a former second-round pick, has struggled to establish himself in the NFL, but the Cowboys are hopeful that he can provide some much-needed help to their passing game. The trade has also been criticized by some, who believe that the Cowboys overpaid for Mingo.

name: Steve Kornacki
summary: Numerous news articles focus on Steve Kornacki's involvement in election coverage. One piece from New York Magazine reveals that he remains uncertain about his role. Another commentary in the Los Angeles Times argues against focusing on Kornacki and his "chartthrobs" during elections. Several articles highlight Kornacki's election preparation and wardrobe, including his signature khakis. NBC Insider provides an interview with Kornacki about his approach to coverage. NBC News and USA TODAY speculate on whether Kornacki will reprise his iconic style this election night. MSNBC reports on Kornacki's analysis of record-breaking 2024 polling. Vulture humorously chronicles Kornacki's meticulous routine on election night. Finally, PEOPLE Magazine explains the factors that will determine the timing of election results, while Out Magazine celebrates Kornacki's popularity among the LGBTQ+ community.

name: Mike Williams
summary: The Pittsburgh Steelers have acquired wide receiver Mike Williams from the New York Jets in a trade that also included edge rusher Preston Smith from the Green Bay Packers. Williams, a seven-year NFL veteran, had drawn interest from multiple teams and is expected to strengthen the Steelers' offense. The Jets received compensation in return for Williams, while the Packers parted ways with Smith to acquire other players. The trade was widely analyzed with experts giving higher marks to the Jets for shedding Williams' substantial contract while adding to their roster. The Steelers hope that Williams' experience and talent will enhance their team, while Williams and other players involved in the trade will have their fantasy football outlook impacted based on their new team situations.

name: Preston Smith
summary: The Pittsburgh Steelers have acquired veteran pass rusher Preston Smith in a trade with the Green Bay Packers. The deal reportedly involved the Steelers giving up a 2025 seventh-round draft pick for Smith. Smith is expected to provide a boost to the Steelers' defense, which has struggled to generate pressure on opposing quarterbacks this season. He has 36 career sacks in six seasons with the Packers and Washington Commanders. Analysts believe the trade is a good move for the Steelers, who were in need of a pass rusher, and a win for the Packers, who were looking for salary cap relief and will receive a draft pick in return.

name: Bernie Marcus
summary: Bernie Marcus, the co-founder of the home improvement retail giant The Home Depot, has passed away at the age of 95. Marcus, a Republican megadonor, was known for his generous support of Jewish causes. His legacy includes establishing The Home Depot Foundation, which has donated billions of dollars to charitable organizations. His death is a significant loss to the business and philanthropic communities.

name: Can you register to vote on Election Day
summary: On Election Day 2024, same-day voter registration will be available in some states, according to CBS News. The New York Times and USA Today provide information on where same-day registration is permitted. Additionally, specific instructions for registering to vote on Election Day are provided by the Daily Montanan for Montana, the Secretary of State of California for California, the University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill for North Carolina, the Milwaukee Journal Sentinel for Wisconsin, and NBC Chicago for Illinois. Information on the upcoming November 5, 2024 General Election is also available from the California Secretary of State. Fairfax County Government NewsCenter offers a comprehensive Voter Guide with information on Election Day 2024 requirements. Lastly, CNET offers a guide on registering and voting in each state, including those that allow registration on Election Day.
